# 02-BACKEND - Backend Development Rules

## Backend Rules Directory

This directory contains all backend development rules for Agent Player.

## Files Structure

### Core Backend Files
- `architecture.mdc` - Clean architecture patterns
- `services.mdc` - Service layer implementation
- `repositories.mdc` - Repository pattern implementation  
- `security.mdc` - Backend security requirements
- `testing.mdc` - Backend testing strategies

## Purpose

Define backend development standards for:
- FastAPI implementation
- SQLAlchemy models
- Clean architecture
- Error handling
- Performance optimization

## Rules Coverage
- Backend architecture patterns
- Database integration
- API implementation
- Security measures
- Testing requirements

## MANDATORY Backend Standards
- All backend code must follow clean architecture
- Repository pattern required for data access
- Service layer for business logic
- Dependency injection for testability
- Async/await for all I/O operations
- Type hints required for all functions
- Error handling with proper logging
- Input validation on all endpoints
- Authentication/authorization where needed
- Database transactions for data consistency

